         

         Contact Managemet App -API based angular project


     1.Create angular project
     2.Install  bootstrap and font awesome.    
     3.Paste cdn link of font awesome in index.html
     4.Conigure  bootstrap and font awesome in angular.json
     5.Configure google  fonts in index.html and style.css.
     6.Check all work.     
     7.Create componets need to display   
        a)Contact manager-view all contact
        b)Add contact-add a new contact
        c)Update contact-to edit existing contact
        d)View contact-to view particular conatct
        e)Page not found- to displa page not found
        f)Nav bar-place its selector inside root component html page
     8.Set up path for each component in order to view it in browser  
        -Set up path for each component in app-routing-module.ts ,routes array
        -In app.component.html add router-outlet selector for displaying different web page as per user request
     9.	Design html page of each component    
     10.	Set up the server api
      	 - Create server folder inside the project
          -Create db.json file
          -	Open cmd from server folder
	            *Create package.json file â€“ command-  npm init
               *Install json-server inside server folder- command-  npm i json-server
      11.Create model  for contact and groups
	         -Create model folder in src folder
           	-Create myContact.ts file
            -Create myGroup.ts file
      12.Create an angular service for making api call  
      13.To get http methods-get,post,put,patch,delete
          -Import HttpClientModule in app.module.ts
      14.Dependency Injection-perform inside constructor (in the file api service.ts)
           -syntax:access specifier variable-name:class-name


         


